### Assign IPAddress to the interface g1 between R1<->R2 as shown in the topology
interface g1
 ip address 10.0.0.2 255.255.255.252
 no shutdown

### Assign IPAddress to the interface g2 between R2<->R3 as shown in the topology
interface g2
 ip address 10.0.0.5 255.255.255.252
 no shutdown

### Assign IPAddress to the interface g3 between R2<->LAN2 (Area2) as shown in the topology
interface g3
 ip address 192.168.2.1 255.255.255.0
 no shutdown

### OSPF
router ospf 1                          
 router-id 2.2.2.2                     
 network 10.0.0.0 0.0.0.3 area 0       ## Advertise link to R1 in Area 0 (backbone)
 network 10.0.0.4 0.0.0.3 area 0       ## Advertise link to R3 in Area 0 (backbone)
 network 192.168.2.0 0.0.0.255 area 2  ## Advertise LAN network in Area 2
 passive-interface g3                 
